## Content Integrity Checklist

This checklist must appear in every draft's Quality Checklist section:

```
### Content Integrity
- [ ] Every client story is classified: [REAL-ANONYMIZED], [ILLUSTRATIVE], or [GENERAL-PRINCIPLE]
- [ ] Story classifications listed in Post Metadata
- [ ] All [REAL-ANONYMIZED] stories trace to experience-inventory.md
- [ ] All [ILLUSTRATIVE] examples use approved framing language
- [ ] No fabricated claims or experience-pattern claims without inventory support
- [ ] No implied guarantees of specific outcomes
- [ ] Compliance rules satisfied
- [ ] Forward-looking projections include qualifying language
```

## When the Inventory Is Unpopulated

If `brand/experience-inventory.md` has not yet been populated:

1. All client stories default to `[ILLUSTRATIVE]` classification
2. All illustrative stories must use approved framing language
3. Authority claims must use knowledge-based framing
4. Personal anecdotes from the voice profile remain available
5. No experience-pattern claims are permitted
